Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.81,0:00:06.69,Narr,,10,10,0,,{\blur3\fscx95}Suspicious about Inspector Ōtaki's odd behaviour, we ended up going with him to a western-style mansion hidden deep in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.42,0:00:13.45,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}There, a group of siblings in a rather uneasy mood gathered together to discuss their inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.24,0:00:19.49,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}The concerned parties were brought to the dining room by the mansion's master via e-mail,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.49,0:00:24.12,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}and they witnessed the master ominously floating outside the window, as a monster flew away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.12,0:00:28.21,Narr,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}That's when we found the second son's dead body.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.21,0:00:36.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeking comprehensive answers, he clears all mysteries and codes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.39,0:00:38.14,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Danger is approaching Ran and Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.14,0:00:40.06,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{\c&H88AA00}Let's solve the mystery behind this bizarre phenomenon!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.06,0:00:41.81,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.81,0:00:43.99,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.99,0:00:46.48,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.19,0:02:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is {\i1}bad{\i0}, Kudō!{（平次）やばいで　工藤！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.66,0:02:39.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! If the murderer was the maid, Hikaru-{\i1}san{\i0},{DORP}{ああ…この殺人が\Nひかるさんの犯行なら→\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.36,0:02:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then it's likely her motive was to avenge her mother's death, who was killed and had her murder disguised as an accident!{DORP}{動機は恐らく　母親を事故に\N見せかけて殺害した者への復讐！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.24,0:02:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the ones who schemed for that accident were the murdered maid Shimizu-{\i1}san{\i0} from half a year ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.61,0:02:51.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the second son, Asanobu-{\i1}san{\i0}, who was killed just now.{そして　それを企てたのが\Nさっき亡くなった麻信さんと→\N}{半年前に亡くなった\Nメイドの清水さん…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if we assume that the eldest daughter, Kamiyo-{\i1}san{\i0}, who still ain't shown up since several hours ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.49,0:03:02.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{守与さんも→その企てに　かんどったとしたら\N}played a part in that plot,{ほんで　だいぶ前から\N姿を見せへん\N}{多分　もう殺害されて→\N遺体は鍵がついた\Nあの冷凍庫ん中や！\N} then maybe she's already been murdered, and her body's been locked inside that freezer!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.79,0:03:06.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the girls are about to open that freezer...{それを今　和葉らが開けようと\Nしとるっちゅうことは…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.63,0:03:09.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The girls are in danger!{蘭たちがヤベエ！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.17,0:03:12.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's open!{（和葉）あっ　開いた。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.63,0:03:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I opened it, Ran-{\i1}chan{\i0}!{開いたでぇ　蘭ちゃん。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.05,0:03:15.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Great!{（毛利　蘭）やったね！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.92,0:03:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, that's some thunder.{ごっつい雷やなぁ。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.21,0:03:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Kinda scary.{うん　なんか怖いよね。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.61,0:03:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, we made a lot of gyōza!{でも　餃子いっぱい焼いたし！}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.84,0:03:27.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{possible typo for POWDER?}Right, right! We'll make it through with all this garlic power!{せやせや！ニンニクパワーで\N乗り切るでぇ！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.48,0:03:30.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!{クソ！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.18,0:03:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it's true!{やっぱりかい！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.90,0:03:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!{和葉！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.78,0:03:35.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}?!{大丈夫？蘭ねえちゃん！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.73,0:03:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hikaru-{\i1}san{\i0}...{ひ　ひかるさんが…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.07,0:03:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!{おい　あんた！（ひかる）ん？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.24,0:03:46.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gyōza?{（平次・コナン）餃子？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:51.67,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hikaru Hinohara (24)\NTorakura Family Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.14,0:03:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Ah, I was so hungry...{んっ。私　お腹がすいてて→\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}And when I smelled the gyōza, I just couldn't resist...{餃子の匂い嗅いだら\N我慢できなくなっちゃって…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sincerely apologise for gorging on them without asking!{ごめんなさい！\N勝手に食べちゃって。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:03:59.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, you've made them so tasty!{でも　とっても\Nおいしくできましたね！\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.80,0:04:01.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, thank you...{ど　どうも…。お～きに…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.72,0:04:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks...{ど　どうも…。お～きに…。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.58,0:04:05.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well? Did you see inside the freezer?{そ　それで？冷凍庫の中　見た？\Nう　うん。\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.83,0:04:06.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.81,0:04:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And something weird was in it...{なんや　けったいなもん\N入っとったよ。\N（平次・コナン）えっ！？\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.09,0:04:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, a large can of dried seaweed...{oy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:19.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's to prevent the seaweed from gettin' moisturised. My mum also regularly puts that in her fridge, but...{\N\N\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.69,0:04:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We don't put in the can itself, do we?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.62,0:04:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.76,0:04:24.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing else inside?{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.62,0:04:28.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, it's a large freezer, and yet...{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.23,0:04:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's pretty weird that the only thing in here is this can.{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:40.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{\N} {\N} {\N\N}Then, what was the trace I saw in front of the freezer that resembled a drag mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.58,0:04:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's in the top compartment?{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.38,0:04:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a freezer too, and it wasn't locked.{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.66,0:04:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And lots of cookin' in there.{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.36,0:04:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you the only one who has\N the key to the freezer, Hikaru-{\i1}san{\i0}?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.59,0:04:54.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I think my master has it too...{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.18,0:04:59.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, are you in charge of all the keys in this mansion?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.34,0:05:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the only keys I have are for this kitchen and the nearby rooms.{\N}{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.30,0:05:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the other maids and butlers are in charge of the rest.{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.14,0:05:13.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but everyone's still awake, right?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.93,0:05:15.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, would you mind callin' them up here?{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.96,0:05:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll treat them to a late night gyōza snack!{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.98,0:05:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I doubt they'd have any appetite after that incident, though.{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.83,0:05:25.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I was pretty hungry.{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.54,0:05:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That... incident?{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.70,0:05:29.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.62,0:05:31.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna know!{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.56,0:05:33.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's all right...{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.13,0:05:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,'Cause almost half of the bizarre phenomena that occurred today have been solved.{has->have?}{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.20,0:05:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if everyone hears the explanation, maybe their appetite will come back, right?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.29,0:05:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you for real? You actually solved the mystery?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.28,0:05:54.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, pretty much.{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:06:01.46,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kishiharu Torakura (45)\N3rd Son of the Torakura Family
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.79,0:06:01.46,Signs,,0,0,0,,Ruri Torakura (38)\NAsanobu's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.54,0:05:58.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}What mystery? Don't we know exactly who the culprit is?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.24,0:06:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Hakuya-{\i1}oniisama{\i0} was the one who killed my husband, right?{\N\}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.92,0:06:08.89,Signs,,0,0,0,,Mina Torakura (26)\N2nd Daughter of the Torakura Family
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.92,0:06:08.89,Signs,,0,0,0,,Jhei Hagawa (29)\NKamiyo's Lover
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.67,0:06:06.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}So did you figure out the reason why our brother turned into a vampire?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.64,0:06:11.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}Well, I understand it's tempting to think of it that way since too much bizarre stuff has happened.{\N\N\N\N\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.22,0:06:14.68,Signs,,0,0,0,,Rikushige Koga (71)\NTorakura Family Butler
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.76,0:06:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\a6}But come on, do vampires really exist?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.99,0:06:18.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can judge it yourself after you see the trick!{\N\N\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.58,0:06:20.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.87,0:06:24.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you telling us that Hakuya-{\i1}niisan{\i0}'s disappearance from the casket was also a trick?{\N\N\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.32,0:06:31.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was a mystery to us back then 'cause we couldn't see any traces of the tiles under the casket havin' been tempered with...{\N}{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.45,0:06:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the {\i1}position{\i0} was off to begin with!{\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.45,0:06:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Position?{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.72,0:06:38.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.50,0:06:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are slits in the middle of the carpet.{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.95,0:06:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And only this portion will come off if we pull it out!{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.19,0:06:49.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if we pull the remaining carpet towards the gap...{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.22,0:06:52.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can see the entrance to the secret passage!{\N\N}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.80,0:06:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Secret passage?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.13,0:07:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}The tiles are part of a sliding door, and a narrow staircase leads to the first floor storage room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.98,0:07:04.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}But there's no staircase in the storage room!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.18,0:07:07.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Only because you didn't notice!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.23,0:07:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}A hidden door that moves with the cabinets serves as a camouflage, that's why.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.74,0:07:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, after that trip, I did notice that the storage room had somehow become narrow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.72,0:07:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That trip?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.97,0:07:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.71,0:07:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Half a year ago, just before the maid Shimizu-{\i1}san{\i0} met her fate,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.44,0:07:30.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the master ordered all of us from the mansion to unwind and took us overseas for a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.55,0:07:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means construction workers were called to make that secret passage during the week.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.10,0:07:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.71,0:07:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get the passage trick, but how did Brother manage to come out of the casket?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.70,0:07:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's easy!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.98,0:07:46.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a sliding door inside the casket, too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.69,0:07:52.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And although it looks like nothing's on the casket lid, there's actually a powerful magnet inside the seams.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.26,0:07:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it looks like it'll be locked tight if you close it...\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:08:01.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until you deactivate it using this remote!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.58,0:08:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.44,0:08:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this remote, the casket, and the secret passage, somebody can freely disappear from inside the casket!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.78,0:08:17.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, then he came out and killed the maid, Shimizu-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.07,0:08:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then was our brother the one who killed Shimizu-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.24,0:08:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.09,0:08:27.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the guards to this mansion weren't hired until after Shimizu-{\i1}san{\i0}'s incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.99,0:08:31.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the crime was performed by callin' Shimizu-{\i1}san{\i0} to the forest beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.16,0:08:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pretendin' to be asleep in the casket, then exitin' to the outside through the storage and goin' for the kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.00,0:08:39.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then where {\i1}is{\i0} our brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.53,0:08:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows? He might be hidin' out somewhere, waitin' for his next victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.74,0:08:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.17,0:08:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we'll be fine if we stick together.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.39,0:08:51.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our opponent isn't a monster, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.74,0:08:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if he was a vampire who could fly or pass through walls, he wouldn't have used a secret passage, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.43,0:09:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's rainin' cats and dogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.77,0:09:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Talk about bad weather!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.97,0:09:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, everybody's late!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.74,0:09:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to think we cooked so many gyōza...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.03,0:09:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Ran-{\i1}chan{\i0}, what do you think Hikaru-{\i1}san{\i0} meant back then by ‘something like that happened’{\fsp-7} ?{\fsp}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.97,0:09:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I dunno, but I'd rather not think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.05,0:09:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the master we saw earlier really was a vampire, then Heiji and the others might've already been bitten and turned into vampires!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way! Are you saying we're the only human beings left in this mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.36,0:09:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.62,0:09:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...can't be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.25,0:09:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, and I'm gettin' hungry after waitin' for so long!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.15,0:09:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't you just eat some?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.09,0:09:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can just cook more when everybody comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.90,0:09:54.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then was the ghost photo taken in this room a trick, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.32,0:09:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Anyway, go ahead to the positions you were in when the photo was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.09,0:10:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.68,0:10:03.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, everybody smile more!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.78,0:10:06.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji-{\i1}niichan{\i0}, relax! Relax!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.10,0:10:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji-{\i1}niichan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.71,0:10:10.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.02,0:10:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nobody in this room but us five.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.46,0:10:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.92,0:10:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.44,0:10:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not a mirror?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a magic mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.43,0:10:29.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like a normal mirror when one side is dark, but if we illuminate the dark side, light will come through just like with glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.27,0:10:34.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's easy to tell them apart, too!\N Just press your finger against it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.60,0:10:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.13,0:10:44.39,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,{\fsp-0.5}With a normal mirror, there'll be a gap between your finger and its reflection, since a reflective coating is applied to the glass's back surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.71,0:10:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But in a magic mirror, the reflective surface is on the front surface of the glass,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.19,0:10:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so an object and its reflection will\N appear to be touching each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.38,0:10:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, if we shine light on it from this side,\N we can see a lot of clothes hanging.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.01,0:11:00.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lot of clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.01,0:11:02.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.32,0:11:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the closet in the next room!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.04,0:11:07.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.88,0:11:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a sliding door on the closet's back wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.11,0:11:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If opened, the magic mirror will appear at the spot where the mirror frame of the next room is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.94,0:11:22.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}And someone hiding in the closet would simply shine light on their face {\N}before the photo was taken
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.47,0:11:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}in order to make a ghost of\N someone's face appear in the mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.33,0:11:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Get it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.43,0:11:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}The culprit had to employ tricks {\N\N}in order to appear as a monster, {\N}but they're still human!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.43,0:11:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}So the culprit really was Hakuya-{\i1}niisan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.41,0:11:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}Yeah, no doubt he's one of the culprits!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.65,0:11:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}{\i1}One{\i0} of the culprits?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.30,0:11:48.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Are you saying there's an accomplice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.81,0:11:52.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}The master was seriously ill, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.04,0:11:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without help, he wouldn't have been able to move about without being seen!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.70,0:12:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}That said, the primary suspect we have as his accomplice {\N\N}is the eldest daughter who's been hiding for so many hours!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.00,0:12:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}Excuse me, the guard at the mansion gate just reported back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.29,0:12:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}He said there's a dead body in the forest in front of the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.49,0:12:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}What now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.90,0:12:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}It's the eldest daughter, Kamiyo-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.35,0:12:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Tied to a stake...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.89,0:12:25.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}She was strangled.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.68,0:12:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the guards, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.44,0:12:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}Did you see anyone who went out with this person?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.64,0:12:39.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}Well, after that Ōtaki guy {\N\N}and a man with a moustache went out by car, nobody left through the gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.30,0:12:43.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{\N\N}It can't be! Then how did they sneak out the gate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.78,0:12:45.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}{\N\N}Did they fly or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.43,0:12:52.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.66,0:12:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}After Ōtaki-{\i1}han{\i0} left in his car, you've\N never opened the mansion gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.94,0:12:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Ah, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}We opened the gate just once.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.29,0:13:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}A van from a furniture company came by.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.33,0:13:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Our chairs were getting old, {\N\N}so the master ordered bulk replacements several days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.86,0:13:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}But when we checked the delivered items, they had a sofa in there by mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.13,0:13:17.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}so we told the van's driver to\N take those back for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.46,0:13:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}That's when the explosion from earlier occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:22.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}From earlier? You mean the collapse of the tunnel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.48,0:13:25.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Yeah. We couldn't look away for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.24,0:13:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}So someone could have slipped out the gate unnoticed by taking advantage of that moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.73,0:13:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}But they would still get spotted if they returned to the mansion {\N\N}after tyin' the body to a stake in this forest, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.44,0:13:40.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Besides, why did the killer stop midway?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.87,0:13:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Midway?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:45.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}Look! There's a hole dug up next to the body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.71,0:13:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}So they planned to tie the body to\N a stake and pin it upside down?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.89,0:13:50.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.04,0:13:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}If this was the same person who killed the maid Shimizu-{\i1}san{\i0} half a year ago, {\N\N}then they might've done it to drain her blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.19,0:14:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Another weird thing is {\N\N}that there's\N a bruise mark on her right biceps.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.29,0:14:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}And what caught my attention the most is the fact that the fingertips on both of her hands sustained friction wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.07,0:14:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}Yeah, and those don't look like\N defensive wounds from fightin' back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.38,0:14:20.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}K-Kamiyo-{\i1}neesan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:22.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}She was killed in the forest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.78,0:14:25.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Are you really sure it was my honey?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.77,0:14:27.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.09,0:14:29.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}N-No. Why?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.70,0:14:33.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, who did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.65,0:14:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}The guards should have seen them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.41,0:14:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}The guards said that after Inspector Ōtaki left by car, no one else entered or exited the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.96,0:14:42.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}No one else?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.21,0:14:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.44,0:14:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}Maybe there are other secret passages like the one before, {\N\N}and someone slipped out the gate through there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.42,0:14:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N}We checked around the wall surrounding the mansion,\Nbut didn't find any place someone could have slipped through.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.96,0:15:00.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{塀の上には\N防犯センサーが付いてて→\N}The guards also mentioned there are security sensors on top of the wall, {誰かが乗り越えたら　すぐに\Nわかるて門番　ゆうとったしなぁ。\N}so they'd know if anyone tried to climb over.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.33,0:15:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{じゃあ　館の中から\Nトンネルとかで？\N}Maybe through a hidden tunnel from inside the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:09.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{旦那さんが館の改装につこたんは一週間やで。\N}But the mansion renovation your brother ordered only lasted a week, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.11,0:15:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そない短い時間で\Nトンネルなんぞ掘れる訳ないやろ。\N}There ain't no way to dig a tunnel that quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.38,0:15:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{バ　バカな！？}Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.80,0:15:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{じゃあ　どうやって\N犯人は門の外に出たんだよ！？\N}Then just how did the killer manage to get out through the gate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.95,0:15:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{しかも姉貴を連れて…。\N}Not to mention, carrying Big Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.84,0:15:21.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{と　飛んだのよ。\N}H-He flew...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.54,0:15:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{吸血鬼になった迫弥お義兄様が\N}Hakuya-{\i1}oniisama{\i0} must've turned into a vampire, {あの　禍々しい翼で…。\N}and by flapping his ominous black wings...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.73,0:15:30.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{あ～っ！！\N落ち着けよ　瑠莉。\N}Calm down, Ruri!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{この若い刑事が言ってただろ。\N吸血鬼なんていねえって。\N}Didn't this young policeman tell us that there's no such thing as a vampire?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.60,0:15:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{刑事？ちゃうちゃう}Policeman? No, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.71,0:15:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{　俺は\N服部平次。大阪の高校生探偵や。\N}I'm Heiji Hattori! A high-school private eye from Ōsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.22,0:15:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{た　探偵？\N}P-Private eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.89,0:15:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{刑事にしちゃ若いと思ってたけど。}I did think you were too young to be a police detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:46.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{高校生のガキかよ。\N}Just some high-school brat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.64,0:15:51.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{まぁ　もう少し調べるよって\Nあんたらまた　この食堂に…あっ！\N}Well, once my investigation progresses a bit further, I'll need you guys to gather in this dinin' room again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.69,0:15:52.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ちょっ…。\N}Hey—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.21,0:15:54.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{冗談じゃないわ！}Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.00,0:15:56.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{刑事だと思って言うこと聞いてたけど。\N}I only listened to you because\N I thought you were with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.35,0:15:59.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{結局ハニーも\N殺されちまったじゃねえか！\N}But see how my honey still got killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.08,0:16:02.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{自分の身は\N自分で守らせてもらうぜ。\N}We'll take care of our own lives from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.58,0:16:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{お　おい　ちょ～待て！\N}H-Hey, wait a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.51,0:16:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{なんだ　刑事さんじゃなかったんですね。\N}Oh. So you're not with the police, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.33,0:16:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{でも　探偵ってことは\N毛利探偵のお弟子さんとか？\N}But by ‘private eye’, do you mean you're Detective Mouri's apprentice or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.96,0:16:16.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{はぁ？何が悲しゅうて\N俺があんなボンクラの…うっ。\N}Huh?! How pathetic does a guy have to be to work under {\i1}that{\i0} dimwit—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.60,0:16:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そ　そうなんや。}D-Damn right you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.26,0:16:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{毛利師匠に→\N\Nもうすぐ免許皆伝\Nもらえそうなんやけど…。\N}Although I'm finally at the point where Master Mouri is about to confer his full mastership on me...{>_>}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.15,0:16:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{へえ…じゃあ　わかります？\N}Then did you figure it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.69,0:16:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{旦那様が体を\Nクルッと回転させたトリック…。}The trick used to rotate Master's body...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.00,0:16:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{回転？\N}Rotate?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.16,0:16:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ほら　食堂の窓の外から　旦那様が\N逆さに首を出したじゃないですか。\N}See, the master's head was upside down{<_<} outside the dining room window, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.99,0:16:45.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{でも　カーテンを開ける前\N稲光に照らされた旦那様の影は→\N}But before the curtains opened, the master's shadow lit up {下から出てたんですよ。\Nあっ！\N}by the lightning came from below,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.20,0:16:48.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N\N}and it looked as if his body was transparent, like a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.03,0:16:57.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{確かここやったな？\N旦那さんの首が見えた窓。\N}This was the window where\N the master's head was seen, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.04,0:16:57.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ。\N}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.34,0:17:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{どや？工藤。}How's it, Kudō?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.05,0:17:05.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{思った通りだぜ。}Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.78,0:17:08.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ってことは\N問題のアレは…。\N}Which means that thing in question...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.22,0:17:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{フン。うまいこと考えよったのう。\N}They really thought this through, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.59,0:17:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{けど　このかなりの大仕掛け…。\N}However, that trick is pretty complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.04,0:17:24.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{急に　この館に来て\Nできるもんやないなあ。\N}It ain't somethin' you could do right after arrivin' at the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.79,0:17:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{なあ　さっきの４人\Nこの館に　よう来てるんか？\N}Say, do the four people just now always come to this mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.43,0:17:37.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{子供の頃　母に連れられてここに来た時は→\N}They were here when I was a child and my mother brought me here,{皆さん\Nいらっしゃいましたけど…。\N} {メイドになってからは\N初めてお会いしましたよ。\N}but it's the first time I've met them since I became a maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.82,0:17:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\N\N}It has been approximately a year since everyone last visited.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.18,0:17:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{皆様　旦那様の様子や容体を→\N\Nよく電話で\Nお尋ねになられるんですが→\N}All of them have been calling me about the master's health and current condition, {なかなかお越しになられなくて…。\N}but no one actually paid a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.04,0:17:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（ひかる）\Nだから私　てっきり皆さんの中の\N誰かが「おめでた」で→\N}In fact, that's why I thought maybe one of them was expecting, {それをお祝いするために　集まら\Nれるんだと思ったんですけどね。\N}and the others gathered here to celebrate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.59,0:18:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{おめでた？\N}Expecting?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.98,0:18:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{だって旦那様　ネットの通販で\N子供用プールとか→\N}Because the master made some online purchases {おもちゃの飛行機とか\N買ってらしたから→\N}for a kiddie pool and a toy aeroplane, {生まれてくる子供への\N贈り物だと思うじゃない！\N}which I thought were gifts for the coming baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.43,0:18:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{メイドになる前は　私にもよく\N服とかプレゼントしてくださってたし。\N}After all, he'd also given me a number of clothes before I became a maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.95,0:18:19.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{その飛行機って　もしかしてはばたくヤツ？\N}Any chance that aeroplane was the type that flaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.31,0:18:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ええ。伝票には\Nそう書いてあったけど→\N}Yeah, it said so on the receipt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.69,0:18:26.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{子供が遊ぶおもちゃにしては\N大きい箱だなと思ったのよね。\N}I thought the box was rather big for a child's toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.50,0:18:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{でも　羽川様と一緒に来られた\N守与様に→\N}But {おめでたのことを　お聞きしたら→\N}I asked Hagawa-{\i1}sama{\i0} and Kamiyo-{\i1}sama{\i0} about whether they were expecting,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.79,0:18:36.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{お二人で「ないない」って\N笑ってらしたし。\N}and they laughed and said, ‘No, nothing like that!’
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.14,0:18:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{その後に来られた岸治様が\N大きなバッグをお持ちだったから→\N}And since Kishiharu-{\i1}sama{\i0}, who arrived afterwards,\N had a large bag with him, {もしかして贈り物？って\N思ったけど…→\N}I thought it had to be a present,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.04,0:18:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{中身はカメラや現像の道具って\N言ってらしたし。→\N}but he told it only had a camera and items for developing photos.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.90,0:18:53.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{君たちが来る　少し前に来られた\N麻信ご夫婦にも聞いたんだけど→\N}I also asked the same thing to the Asanobu couple, who came a little before you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.94,0:18:58.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{「実那さん　羽川様と寄りが戻った\Nのかしら？」って　瑠莉さんが…。\N}to which Ruri-{\i1}san{\i0} replied, ‘Could it be that Mina-{\i1}san{\i0} made up with Hagawa-{\i1}kun{\i0}?’
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.76,0:19:01.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{じゃあ　実那さんにも聞いたの？}So you asked Mina-{\i1}san{\i0} the same question too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.01,0:19:04.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ええ。君たちの少しあとに\N来られたから…→\N}Yeah, since she came a little after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.08,0:19:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ガン無視されちゃったけど。\N}But she ignored me completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.18,0:19:11.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{寄りが戻るっちゅうことは→\N}‘Made up’{\fsp-6} {\fsp}? So Hagawa-{\i1}san{\i0} \Nand Mina-{\i1}san{\i0} were dating?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.78,0:19:12.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{はい。\N}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.56,0:19:18.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ですが　熱烈な実那様の求婚が→\N\N羽川様には\Nかなり負担だったようで…→\N}But Mina-{\i1}sama{\i0}'s fiery proposal apparently caused Hagawa-{\i1}sama{\i0} a great deal of burden,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.86,0:19:21.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{いつのまにか守与様と。\N}so lo and behold, he came to be with Kamiyo-{\i1}sama{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.44,0:19:24.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ほんなら　岸治さんと瑠莉さんは？\N}Well then, what about Kishiharu-{\i1}san{\i0} and Ruri-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.24,0:19:35.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{お二人は…→\N\N元々婚約なさっていたんですが→\N}They were engaged, {陽子様が\Nあの事故で亡くなられたあと→\N}but after Yōko-{\i1}sama{\i0}'s accidental death, {岸治様が　ひどく落ち込まれて\N婚約は破談となり→\N}Kishiharu-{\i1}sama{\i0} became severely depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.83,0:19:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{瑠莉様は　麻信様に\N見初められてご結婚を。\N}Their engagement dissolved, and Ruri-{\i1}sama{\i0} fell in love with Asanobu-{\i1}sama{\i0}, which led to their marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.34,0:19:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{どうやら岸治様は　旦那様の\N婚約者だった陽子様のことが→\N}Apparently, Kishiharu-{\i1}sama{\i0} had been very fond {本当に　お好きだったようで\Nございます。\N}of Yōko-{\i1}sama{\i0}, who was the master's fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:53.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{陽子様の葬儀の日　旦那様よりも\N泣いてらしたので…。\N}He cried even more profusely than the master on the day of Yōko-{\i1}sama{\i0}'s funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.14,0:19:58.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{でも　執事さんも\Nかなり泣いてらしたって→\N}But the maids said that you, Mr. Butler, also wept many tears, {メイドさんたちが言ってましたよ。\N}or so I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.64,0:20:01.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{母ととても\N仲が良かったからだろうって…。\N}Adding that you must have been \Non great terms with my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.33,0:20:03.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そ　そんなことは…。\N}T-That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.34,0:20:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{なんかドロドロしてんなぁ。\N}All of that sounded pretty sordid to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.36,0:20:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ。みんなにそれぞれ\N動機ありそうやのぉ。\N}Yeah. It looks like everybody has a motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.37,0:20:14.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（メールの着信音）\Nあ　岸治さんからメール。\N}Ah, an e-mail from Kishiharu-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.72,0:20:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{部屋にお酒を持ってきてくれ…か。\N}Asking me to bring alcohol to his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.66,0:20:20.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{あの人　あんたのメルアド知っとるんか？\N}So he knows your e-mail address?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（ひかる）\N岸治さんだけじゃないですよ。\N}Not just Kishiharu-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.04,0:20:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ここへ来られる前の日に→\N}I also e-mailed everyone {「お待ちしてます」ってメールを\N皆さんに送りましたから。\N}with an ‘I'll be waiting for you’ the day before they arrived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.40,0:20:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{何で　わざわざ？\N}Why go the extra mile?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.35,0:20:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{この前　旦那様が　皆さんのメルアドを\Nメールで教えて下さったから…。\N}Because not long ago, the master gave me\N all of their e-mail addresses via e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.39,0:20:40.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{きっと「皆さんが来られる前に\N挨拶しておきなさい」って→\N\Nことだろうと思って　メールを。\N}I figured that it was a hint for me to welcome everyone before they came, so I sent the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.40,0:20:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{私　旦那様と\Nよくメールしてるので。\N}The master and I often message each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.26,0:20:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ほんなら　もしかして「南蛮部屋に\N来い」って言われたんも…。\N}Then when he told you to ‘come to\N the foreign torture room’, it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.05,0:20:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ええ　メールで…}Yes, via e-mail!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.31,0:20:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ほら！\N}See!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.04,0:20:54.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,‘After breakfast, come to the foreign torture room without telling anyone.’
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.94,0:20:57.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,‘Whatever you do, don't alert the butler.’
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:01.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{でも　このメール見たのが\Nお昼過ぎで…。\N}But I didn't see this message until after noon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.58,0:21:05.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{それもあって　旦那様と会うのを\Nすっぽかしちゃったのよね。\N}That's also why I skipped out on his meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.64,0:21:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{メールに気づかなかったの？\N}You didn't notice the e-mail?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.79,0:21:11.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{私　洗面所で携帯充電してたのを\Nすっかり忘れてて。\N（メールの着信音）\N}I left my phone charging at the toilet's basin{oy...} and forgot about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.71,0:21:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{わ！岸治さんから催促のメール…\N}Kishiharu-{\i1}san{\i0}'s urging me to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.15,0:21:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{私　行ってきますね。\N}Please excuse me then!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.09,0:21:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{メールの文面からすると…。}Judging from the message...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.37,0:21:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{とても旦那さんに嫌われてる\Nようには見えへんのぉ…。\N}It didn't seem like the master hated her or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.98,0:21:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{（和葉）ウソォ！みんな\N餃子食べにけぇへんの？\N}No way! No one's coming to eat our gyōza?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.49,0:21:29.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{寝てもうたん？}Are they all asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.16,0:21:33.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{いえ　皆さん　起きてらっしゃると\N思うんですけど…。\N}No, I think everyone's still awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.25,0:21:34.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そういう気分じゃないかと。\N}But I guess they're just not in the mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.57,0:21:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{とにかく　あなたたちは\N早くお休みになった方が…。\N}At any rate, I reckon it'd be best if you two also went to bed soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.14,0:21:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そんなぁ…\N}No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.04,0:21:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{せっかく　おいしく焼けたのに。\N}They're so tasty, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.99,0:21:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ちゅうても　２人であらかた\N食べてもうたやん。\N}But then again, the two of us almost gobbled them all up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.72,0:21:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そうだね。}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.42,0:21:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{コナン君たちが食べに来たらどうしよう。\N}What do we do if Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0} and the others come to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.93,0:21:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{材料まだあるし\N}We still have some ingredients left,\N {また作ったらええんちゃう？\N}so we could just make more, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.88,0:22:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{犯人は　あの人に間違いない…\Nそうやな　工藤。\N}The killer has to be that person, right, Kudō?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.70,0:22:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{ああ。だが証拠が何もねえ。\N}Yeah. But we don't have any proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.19,0:22:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.41,0:22:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way Kamiyo-{\i1}san{\i0} was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.82,0:22:12.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{そのトリックが解けへんことには\Nどうにもでけへん。\N}Yeah, we still have an unsolved trick at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.30,0:22:19.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How did the killer pass through the gates, and murder Kamiyo-{\i1}san{\i0} in the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.85,0:23:46.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is my daughter still okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.55,0:24:01.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now it's perfectly clear — our opponent ain't some vampire with wings!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.14,0:24:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.47,0:24:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an evil creature all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.62,0:24:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's a murderer rather than a vampire!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.90,0:24:13.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,(FOUR)
